claim.claim-text:
1. A power conversion device, comprising: 
a first switching element (21), one main electrode thereof being connected to a first source line (PP); 
a first freewheeling diode (22) connected to said first switching element (21) in inverse-parallel; 
a second switching element (24), one main electrode thereof being connected to other main electrode of said first switching element (21), and other main electrode thereof being connected to a second source line (NN); 
a second freewheeling diode (25) connected to said second switching element (24) in inverse-parallel; 
a third switching element (31), one main electrode thereof being connected to said first source line (PP); 
a third freewheeling diode (32) connected to said third switching element (31) in inverse-parallel; 
a fourth switching element (34), one main electrode thereof being connected to other main electrode of said third switching element (31), and other main electrode thereof being connected to said second source line (NN); 
a fourth freewheeling diode (35) connected to said fourth switching element (34) in inverse-parallel; 
a capacitor (12), one end and other end thereof being connected to said first source line (PP) and said second source line (NN), respectively; 
a first switch (11), one end thereof being connected to one source line of a set of said first source line (PP) and said second source line (NN); 
an initial charging circuit (6) having a DC power source (16) and a second switch (18) connected in series, one end thereof being connected to a connection between said third switching element (41) and said fourth switching element (44), and other end thereof being connected to said second source line (NN); and 
an initial charge controller unit (70) controlling said second switch (18) and said second switching element (24) so as to set said second switch (18) ON and repeatedly turn ON and OFF said second switching element (24) while said first switch (11) is set OFF.

20. The power conversion device according to claim 1, further comprising: 
a fifth switching element (41), one main electrode thereof being connected to said first source line (PP); 
a fifth freewheeling diode (42) connected to said fifth switching element (41) in inverse-parallel; 
a sixth switching element (44), one main electrode thereof being connected to other main electrode of said fifth switching element (41), and other main electrode thereof being connected to said second source line (NN); and 
a sixth freewheeling diode (45) connected to said sixth switching element (44) in inverse-parallel.
